===Alternative forms===
* [[behaviour]] (everywhere except US)
* {{l|en|behavoure}}, {{l|en|behavier}}, {{l|en|behavor}}, {{l|en|behavour}}

===Etymology===
From {{suffix|behave|ior|lang=en}}, apparently in simulation of {{term|havior|lang=en}}, {{term|haviour|lang=en}}, {{term|havour|lang=en}}. Compare {{etyl|sco|-}} {{term|havings||behavior|lang=sco}}, from {{term|have||to behave|lang=sco}}.

===Pronunciation===
* {{a|GenAm}} {{IPA|[bəˈheɪvjɚ]|lang=en}}
* {{a|RP}} {{IPA|[bəˈheɪvjə]|lang=en}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|-|s}} {{label|en|American spelling}}

# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} Human conduct relative to social norms.
# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} The way a living creature [[behave]]s or [[act]]s generally.
# {{context|uncountable|informal|lang=en}} A state of probation about one's conduct.
#: ''He was on his best '''behavior''' when her family visited.''
# {{context|countable|lang=en}} An instance of the way a living creature behaves.
# {{context|countable|uncountable|biology|psychology|lang=en}} Observable response produced by an organism.
# {{context|uncountable|lang=en}} The way a device or system operates.

